As you &quot;can not use CSS&quot; here are the two issues with your code...

Firstly, you&#39;re trying to do a numerical operation on a string

    if (animal[i] % 2 === 0)

Your array contains string items, therefore this is (as [04FS says in their comment](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58321805/how-to-color-in-blue-every-even-value-from-the-array-in-an-ul-element-with-jav/58322167#comment103002470_58321805)) effectively saying

    if (&quot;Dog&quot; % 2 === 0)

So instead, just check the **index**...

    if (i % 2 === 0)

Secondly, you&#39;re then trying to set a CSS style on the string object in the array, which obviously isn&#39;t going to work, because &quot;dog&quot; doesn&#39;t have a `style` property

    animal[i].style.color = &#39;0000FF&#39;;

You should be setting it on the `li` object you&#39;ve just created...

    li.style.color = &#39;0000FF&#39;;

So the result should be...

    if (i % 2 === 0) {
